data.enText: more attractive or more suitable; to be preferred to sth

data.chText: 什么都比家里的紧张气氛好。
data.enText: Anything was preferable to the tense atmosphere at home.

data.chText: 他觉得乡村生活比都市生活称心得多。
data.enText: He finds country life infinitely preferable to living in the city.

data.chText: 雇请两个人比雇请一个更好。
data.enText: It would be preferable to employ two people, not one.

data.chText: 我们正在找新房子，最好是靠近学校的。
data.enText: We're looking for a new house, preferably one near the school.

value.def: If you say that one thing is preferable to another, you mean that it is more desirable or suitable.

example.ex: A big earthquake a long way off is preferable to a smaller one nearby...
example.tran: 远处发生大地震总比在附近发生小地震好。

example.ex: The hazards of the theatre seemed preferable to joining the family paint business...
example.tran: 经营剧院的风险似乎比加入家族涂料产业的风险要小一些。

example.ex: Was an evening with Peter in their company preferable to being left at home alone?
example.tran: 晚上和彼得在他们的公司呆着是不是比一个人留在家里好一些？

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, usu ADJ <l>to</l> n/-ing, <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf/that

value.tran: 更好的；更可取的；更合适的

example.ex: Do something creative or take exercise, preferably in the fresh air.
example.tran: 做一些有创意的事情或者运动一下，最好是在空气新鲜的户外进行。
